Beijing market supervision department to carry out comprehensive law enforcement before the festival of commodity prices basically stable
China New Network Beijing September 27th (Reporter Du Yan) In order to strengthen the pre-holiday market supervision and law enforcement, the Beijing Municipal Market Supervision Bureau inspected more than 2000 households on the eve of the National Day.
The inspection situation shows that the market sales of grain and oil, meat, fruit, vegetables, eggs and other necessities of life supply are sufficient, commodity prices are basically stable, no serious violations have been found, and the market operation order is generally stable.
Today, the reporter learned from the Beijing Municipal Market Supervision Bureau that the bureau has carried out "comprehensive law enforcement inspection day" activities in the city, focusing on price, industry and commerce, quality supervision, food and medicine, commerce and other elements, all-round law enforcement inspection, and comprehensively standardizing the market management order.
According to reports, the Beijing Municipal Market Supervision Bureau price, industry and commerce, quality supervision, food and medicine, commerce and other five law enforcement teams, close cooperation, by the heads of various law enforcement agencies led the team, the randomized part of the business entities for joint law enforcement inspection.
In the inspection, law enforcement officials focused on price behavior, advertising, food safety, measurement standards, production safety system and other content to check.
The district market supervision bureau has also organized joint law enforcement inspections simultaneously, dispatched more than 1600 times to law enforcement personnel, inspected more than 2000 households in various business entities, and the inspection shows that the market sells grain and oil, meat, fruits, vegetables, egg milk and other necessities.
The Beijing Municipal Market Supervision Bureau said that during the National Day, it will strengthen emergency duty, continue to carry out inspections and inspections of the market, quickly handle various market supervision issues in accordance with the law, and deal with the business violations reflected by the people. Once verified, it will be dealt with seriously in accordance with the law and earnestly safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of consumers.
Confucius Institute of the Royal Cambodian Academy of Sciences "China in My Heart" Chinese essay contest revealed
The Chinese essay contest "China in My Heart" with the theme of the 70th anniversary of New China was unveiled and an award ceremony was held on the 26th at the Confucius Institute of the Royal Cambodian Academy of Sciences.
The Chinese Embassy Diplomat Zhong Zhifa, the Cambodian-Chinese Councilor, and Wei Siyu, President of the Jiangxi Chamber of Commerce in Cambodia, presented awards to the winners.
According to Chai Keqing, Chinese president of the Confucius Institute of the Royal Cambodian Academy of Sciences, the competition lasted for two months, and the participants were for Cambodian students, secondary school students (including special students) and university students (including social personnel).
The Chinese Embassy in Cambodia, a diplomat, Zhongzhen Law, presented the winning certificate for the first prize winner of the university group, and Guo Lina, winner of the first prize of the primary and secondary school group.
Chai Keqing said that the entries are carried out separately according to the university group and the primary and secondary school groups, and invited senior Chinese experts from Cambodia to form a review committee, through the preliminary evaluation, review, final evaluation, etc., and finally selected the first prize of the university group, the second prize of 2, the third prize 3, the outstanding award 10; the first prize of the first prize of the primary and secondary school groups, the second prize 5th, the third prize of 10, the excellent award.
Lin Weicai, a first prize winner of the university group, said that it has been 15 years since learning Chinese, which has had a huge impact on himself.
Through the essay contest, it is written to describe the benefits brought to Cambodia under the "Belt and Road" and the traditional friendship between China and Cambodia, and hope that the younger generation will continue to contribute to China-Cambodia friendship.
Pictured are guests and winners.
Guo Lina, winner of the first prize of the primary and secondary school group, said that as an overseas Chinese, he had the opportunity to express the "China in my heart" through the words of his native nationality and win the award, and there was a different kind of excitement.
The organizers said that through the competition, it has not only created a positive atmosphere for China-Cambodia relations, but also attracted more and more Cambodian students to study in Chinese and study in China.
The United Nations International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) reported on the 26th that Iran has begun to use advanced centrifuges to accelerate the production of enriched uranium, further violating the 2015 nuclear agreement with the world powers.
The IAEA report notes that advanced centrifuges at the Natanz Nuclear Facility at Iran's Natanz Nuclear Facility are "building or are ready to build up to enrich uranium."
Since U.S. President Donald Trump withdrew from the nuclear deal in May and imposed sanctions on Iran, Iran is gradually violating the restrictions of the 2015 nuclear deal with the major powers.
The agreement stipulates that Iran can only use the first generation of IR-1 centrifuges to extract uranium.
The other signatories to the deal, Britain, China, France, Germany and Russia, have been trying to salvage it, but Tehran has repeatedly accused Europe of not doing enough.
