Tuionettoa was elected as Tonga's new prime minister.
Nukualofa news: The South Pacific island nation of Tonga's parliament elected on the 27th, the current Minister of Finance and National Planning, Pohiwa Tuonettoa, as Tonga's new prime minister, replacing former Prime Minister Akilisi Pohiwa, who died of illness earlier this month.
According to the main Tongan media outlet, the MATLAB Parliament is a one-edition system, which is composed of 26 MPs.
In the day's parliamentary vote, Tuioneta received 23 votes in support, beating rival Deputy Prime Minister and Minister for Infrastructure and Tourism, Semysi Sika, to be successfully elected.
Tonga is a constitutional monarchy, with a system of separation of powers in the executive, legislative and judicial branches.
Tuioneta is still required to accept the appointment of the king.
The next Tonga parliamentary elections will be held in 2021.
