Garbage classification education first into Jilin kindergarten environmental protection concept from the doll grabbed
On the 27th, a kindergarten in Jilin City, Jilin Province, conducted a garbage sorting class to teach young children to distinguish between recyclable and other types of garbage.
It is reported that this is the first time that garbage classification has entered the local early childhood education classroom.
Recently, Jilin Province nine departments jointly issued the "Jilin Province to promote the classification and treatment of prelander urban domestic waste work plan."
In 2019, on the basis of the pilot of the compulsory classification of domestic waste in Changchun, the province decided to carry out the classification of domestic waste in prefecture-level cities.
Jilin is one of them.
Through this event, we hope to achieve the effect of driving the family with young children and driving the society in kindergarten, and advocate the concept of environmental protection.
Liu Lijuan, executive director of the Hi Fan Children International Kindergarten, who held the event, said.
On the same day, the director read out the environmental initiative, hoping that the garbage sorting would start with the child.
The children made a small game of garbage sorting after performing the "Low Carbon Bei Bei" dance.
The instructor also issued the "recyclable" and "other garbage" label, suggesting that the children stick the label to the trash can and record the little video when they get home.
Liu Lijuan introduced that the kindergarten has always advocated the concept of low-carbon and green environmental protection, and regularly opened environmental protection lecture halls.
The garbage drop in the park also has a sortable garbage can set up, which is marked with the drop category.
The teacher taught the children what is recyclable garbage.
According to preliminary statistics, Jilin Province in 2018 urban domestic waste generated about 546.52 million tons, all into the domestic waste disposal site for processing.
Among them, sanitary landfill 329.29 million tonnes, incineration 209.23 million tonnes, the comprehensive utilization process is treated with 8.01 million tonnes.
After years of efforts, all cities and counties in the province have the ability to treat domestic waste harmlessly.
In the "Jilin Province Promotion of Land-level Urban Waste Classification and Treatment Work Program", the work plan for the classification of prefecture-level urban waste is clearly required to carry out in-depth activities such as garbage classification into the campus, into teaching materials, and into the classroom, and strengthen the interaction between students and parents by creating works such as garbage classification songs, songs, comics, micro-videos, and achieve the effect of "education of a child, affecting a family, driving a community, and training a new generation of new people".
