Some members of the Legislative Council of the Hong Kong SAR issued a joint statement on the 27th, expressing strong opposition to the passage of the "Hong Kong Human Rights and Democracy Act 2019" by the Foreign Affairs Committee of the United States Congress.
The statement, co-sponsored by 40 establishment lawmakers, said that the rights currently enjoyed by Hong Kong are conferred by the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, including maintaining the status of the free trade port and the separate customs territory, and entering into bilateral and multilateral agreements in the name of "Hong Kong, China" in different fields such as economy, finance, shipping, trade, communications, tourism, culture, and sports, and the signing and implementation of bilateral and multilateral agreements.
These rights are not administered by any foreign government or legislature.
Hong Kong has always strictly abided by international agreements, international rules, laws and business ethics, discussed with different countries and regions, and participated in many relevant fields.
The statement said that the move of the United States Senate and House Foreign Affairs Committee to pass the relevant bill is not necessary, but only to respond to the call of its bane Hong Kong agent, as a means of grossly interfering in Hong Kong's internal affairs and to fight for political chips for its agents in Hong Kong.
The establishment lawmakers expressed deep regret and strongly opposed the move.
The statement noted that Hong Kong is an important trading partner of the United States and the largest source of trade surpluses.
Hong Kong's excellent rule of law, a fair and free business environment, and a clean society make it a good location for American businessmen to do business.
If the United States passes this bill, in addition to hitting the interests of Hong Kong and the United States itself, it will make China-US relations worse, and have no benefit, and will damage others.
The statement said that Hong Kong will, as always, unswervingly implement the "one country, two systems" policy, continue to enjoy the rights enshrined in the Basic Law and earnestly fulfill its obligations.
Whether past, present or future, Hong Kong will continue to make its due contribution to the international community and international commerce.
According to the European Times on the 26th, the two houses of the French parliament will discuss immigration policy reform next week.
French President Emmanuel Macron recently claimed that France could not "accept everyone", but at the same time he would try to "properly accept".
Macron is trying to find a compromise on immigration matters, slowing the impact of the upcoming debate.
Recently, Macron said in an interview during the general debate of the UN General Assembly in New York that he hoped to have a real "two-pronged" solution on immigration policy to find a balance between humanitarianism and efficiency.
Macron said: "If France wants to be able to properly admit (immigrants), it cannot accept everyone."
Macron cited four priorities of immigration policy: granting asylum as soon as possible to refugees in need of protection; promoting the integration of migrants more efficiently; hosting and protecting all migrants entering French territory; and more efficiently resettle people who entered France illegally and should not stay.
Whether illegal immigrants should be protected by the "National Medical Assistance" system is the most discussed topic in the past.
Macron said he wanted to be able to "assess" the system, but not to lift it, but to limit it.
After Macron's remarks, Le Pen, leader of the far-right "National Alliance," tweeted that Macron's statement was "empty talk."
Lassher, a right-wing Republican and president of the Senate, also said that immigration policy should be discussed in a "de-escalation" but "face reality" and indirectly criticized Macron.
Valau, a left-wing Socialist lawmaker, believes that France should "accept more and better" on immigration issues, and criticized Macron for "manipulating" the issue.
The new asylum and immigration law, which has been enacted for a year, has led to disagreements within the ruling party, but at the same time is unable to placate the right-wing opposition party.
In the next 2022 election, the topic of immigration policy will once again be the focus of far-right attacks, and Macron needs to make a difference on this issue, but at the same time risking angering leftists within the ruling party.
According to reports, the lower house of the French National Assembly will debate immigration policy from September 30, and the Senate will debate it from October 2.
There are signs that China's A-shares are ushering in a "repurchase tide", and many listed companies have come up with "real gold and silver" to buy back the company's shares.
According to the statistics of financial data service provider Oriental Fortune, as of the 27th, the total amount of repurchase implementation of A-share listed companies in 2019 has exceeded 100 billion yuan (yuan, the same below), far exceeding the data of the same period in previous years, setting a record high in the amount of A-share share repurchase funds.
In this regard, Xu Yang, chairman of Shanghai Mai Kerong Information Consulting Co., Ltd., said that the overall valuation of the A-share market this year is low, and the share is repurchased at a relatively low price at a relatively low price, which is conducive to the improvement of the efficiency of the use of funds by listed companies, and also reflects the willingness of listed companies to actively manage the market value and the abundant cash flow situation, which is conducive to boosting investor confidence.
In addition, the continuous improvement of the share repurchase system has also promoted listed companies to actively carry out share repurchases.
For example, at the beginning of this year, the Shanghai Stock Exchange and the Shenzhen Stock Exchange issued the implementation rules for the repurchase of shares of listed companies, providing listed companies with detailed share repurchase norms and guidelines.
According to media statistics, since this year, listed companies that have implemented repurchase plans have been mainly concentrated in the infrastructure industry, real estate industry, information technology industry and electronic equipment manufacturing industry.
In addition, from the perspective of the amount of repurchase payment, six listed companies have repurchased more than 1 billion yuan this year.
Among them, the first place is Yili shares, and its repurchase amount is more than half a billion yuan.
What impact will the repurchase of shares in public companies have on the market?
Zhao Xijun, vice dean of the School of Finance and Finance of Renmin University of China, said in an interview with the China News Agency that on the one hand, the repurchase shows that listed companies have strong economic strength and good financial situation, and have the ability to maintain the stability of stock prices and give investors confidence; on the other hand, it also shows that listed companies and their controlling shareholders are responsible to the company, are responsible for the market and responsible for investors.
The former is based on the company's good operating performance, and the latter requires listed companies and their controlling shareholders to have higher quality.
For the capital market, this is the core of the basic elements.
The repurchase of shares by listed companies is conducive to boosting investor confidence and exerting a supporting effect on the stock price of listed companies.
According to the Oriental Securities Research Report, according to the number of projected stock repurchases set by A-share listed companies since the beginning of this year, as well as the average price of the repurchase of shares, the incremental funds brought by the repurchase of shares for the A-share market this year are expected to break through the 15bn yuan.
In the past two months, the restoration of the large mural "After the Heavenly Holy Land" of Tianjin Tiangyao, a national key cultural protection unit, was announced on the 26th, and the restoration of the Great Mural "After Heavenly" was announced, and it will be reopened to the outside world during the National Day this year.
The shrine of the afterlife is a large-scale traditional mural that fully reflects the life of the mother.
With the approval of the relevant departments of the state, Cai Changkui, director of the former Tianjin Civic Museum (Heavenly Palace), was painted from 1991 to 1994.
It is understood that this mural is painted on the south and south of the main hall of the Heavenly Palace, the southern and north palace walls, the full length of 32 meters, the height of 2.6 meters, divided into two parts, with the after-the-day birth, take the sea, the sun ascension and other more than 30 stories, 358 personal belongings reproduce the life of the mother.
Cai Changkui said that in recent years, Tianjin has been rainy in summer and dry in winter, which has caused the mural to rupture, and the rupture part accounts for 60% of the entire area of the mural.
In order to protect and rescue the mural of Mazu, the Tianjin Nankai District Ancient Culture Street Management Committee and Tianyi Palace have launched the restoration of the Temple of Heaven and the Temple of the Temple of the Temple.
The restoration project was led by Cai Changkui, and four famous national painters were invited to participate together.
The restoration work is based on the principle of "repairing the old as old", and the original mural has been adjusted for local content, and the original place where the mural is not perfect has been supplemented by restoration.
In the restoration, we have also made innovations and attempts in terms of color, materials, pen and ink.
After the restoration, the original mural, the style, spirituality, spirit and art style were maintained.
The palace was built in 1326, the original name of the Tiantian Palace, commonly known as the maiden palace, after many renovations, is the oldest building complex in downtown Tianjin, and is also one of the earliest mazu temples in China's extant years.
On September 25th, the Beijing Daxing International Airport's inauguration ceremony was solemnly held.
The shape of the Beijing Daxing International Airport terminal means "phoenix wings", known as the "new world of the seventh miracle".
At present, Beijing Capital International Airport is already overloaded, and last year carried 100 million passengers, becoming the second annual passenger throughput in the world after the Atlanta Airport in the United States.
It is expected that by 2022, Beijing Daxing International Airport passenger throughput will reach 45 million passengers, accounting for 20% of international flights; by 2025, passenger throughput will reach 72 million, and the proportion of international flights is expected to reach 30%.
As a "new country", how cool is it?
Beijing Daxing International Airport is located between Beijing Daxing District and Langfang City, Hebei Province, with a straight distance of 46km from Tiananmen, and is currently the largest new airport built in the world.
The ground projection area of its terminal's roof cover steel architecture reaches 180,000 square meters, with the size of 25 standard football fields.
Beijing Daxing International Airport is the world's first terminal with two arrivals and two departures - F1-F4 is international arrival, domestic arrival, domestic departure, and international departure.
The two-storey bridge connecting the high-speed and the airport outside the terminal, which corresponds to the terminal F3, F4 - the international departure level, and the two floors of domestic departure can be.
The first flight of Beijing Daxing International Airport opened the era of Beijing's "Double Airport".
The new airport is positioned as a large international aviation hub, the development of a new power source, and the Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei regional integrated transportation hub that supports the construction of Xiong'an New Area. Up to now, a total of 66 airlines are interested in entering Beijing Daxing International Airport. Among them, 20 domestic airlines, 46 Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan regions and foreign airlines have been approved for flights.
In the winter and spring season, Beijing Daxing International Airport is expected to open 116 routes, of which 101 domestic routes and 15 international routes; covering 112 destinations around the world, including 97 domestic destinations and 15 international destinations.
This is a "dual hub" airport pattern with Beijing Capital International Airport that has a coordinated development, moderate competition and international first-class competitiveness, which not only eases the operating pressure of the capital airport's capacity, but also better meets the urgent needs of the rapid growth of air transport in Beijing and surrounding areas, and effectively enhances the international competitiveness of China's civil aviation industry.
In order to ensure efficiency and quality, Beijing Daxing International Airport fully considers the relationship between the geographical location and the surrounding airspace and the operating environment. For the first time, the airport runway adopts the "full-oriented" layout in China, adopts the world's largest air traffic control system, and establishes China's largest terminal control area to maximize the efficiency of aviation operation.
For the first time, domestic airports of this scale have used a domestic baggage automatic processing and information management system, using an innovative baggage transmission mode to improve the efficiency of baggage system processing.
The maiden voyage of Beijing Daxing International Airport indicates that the phoenix spreads its wings to take off.
This new airport, which has created more than 40 international and domestic first, and the localization rate has reached more than 98%, which will have a direct and indirect economic impact on the industry in the surrounding areas, and injects air vitality into Beijing's economic development.
