The deepest silo of our railway is dug to the end.
Xinhua News Agency Kunming September 27th (Reporter Ding Yiquan) According to the news of China Railway Tunnel Bureau Group Co., Ltd., the first long tunnel of China's railway - Da (Li) Railway Gaolig Mountain Tunnel 1st shaft main well on the 27th successfully dug into the end, the depth of the well 762.59 meters broke the deepest record of the domestic railway shaft.
In the tunnel construction, the shaft can play a role in improving tunnel ventilation, improving the efficiency of the ball, and ensuring construction safety.
Song Tao, chief engineer of the Great Wells of the Great Project Department of the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, said: "After the successful excavation of the main well of the shaft of the No. 1 of the Gao Ligong Mountain Tunnel, it will help promote the construction of the construction of the bottom of the well, open multiple work surfaces for the later construction of the main hole and flat guide, and accelerate the construction progress of the entire Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel."
Song Tao introduced that the construction of the 1st shaft of the Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel adopts the well-taching method, equipped with the "four-in-one" mechanized assembly line such as the well-taching shaft, the well-tangling, the well-cuting car, the entire mobile metal template, the FJD-6A type of the mechmary diamond machine, the formation of the mechanized process such as the mechanized process such as the mechanized excavation system, the lifting system, the hanging system, the winch lifting system, and the "four-in-one" mechanization line, which realizes the all-in-one process of the eye, blasting, the ball, the ball, the installation of the concrete and pouring.
It is understood that the Da Rui Railway is from Dali to the east, west to Ruili, the full length of about 331 kilometers, the design speed of 140 kilometers per hour, is an important part of the China-Myanmar international railway channel.
The high-rise Mount Tunnel is 34.538 km long and is the first long tunnel of China's railway.
