During the year, the repurchase scale of listed companies exceeded 100bn yuan, which reached a record high - Xinhua
In order to stabilize the company's stock price and maintain the company's image, listed companies have begun to repurchase shares frequently in the past two years, and through targeted repurchases, collection bidding transactions, etc., they hope to pass on the information that the company's value is underestimated to the market, thereby stabilizing the stock price and enhancing investor confidence.
Oriental Wealth Choice data show that in 2017, the funds used by listed companies to buy back shares were 79 billion yuan, which surged to 5.10 billion yuan in 2018. Since 2019, the total amount of A-share listed companies' repurchase implementation has exceeded 100 billion yuan, setting a new high in the amount of A-share repurchase funds in the history of repurchase funds, and far exceeds the previous year.
From the point of view of the purpose of repurchase, the company's repurchase of shares and the increase of major shareholders seems to be the same, but there are big differences in the implementation of the main body, the source of funds, the repurchase use, the stock itself's
Xu Yang, chairman of Shanghai Mai Kerong Information Consulting Co., Ltd., said in an interview with the "Securities Daily" reporter that the "Opinions on Supporting Listed Companies to Repurchase Shares" issued in November 2018, for the problems of the current system such as the narrow scope of share repurchase, complex decision-making procedures, and the imperfect inventory system have been repaired, due to the previous policy from the policy to encourage listed companies to buy back shares, so the phenomenon of repurchased shares in that year has increased significantly.
In January this year, the Shanghai Stock Exchange and the Shenzhen Stock Exchange officially issued the Regulations on the Implementation of Repurchases of Shares by Listed Companies, which have broadened the source of repurchase of listed companies, appropriately simplified the implementation procedures, guided and improved governance arrangements, and encouraged all kinds of listed companies to implement equity incentives or employee stock ownership plans.
After the introduction of the opinions, the operation of the listed company to carry out share repurchase, with more applicable circumstances, the repurchase process is simpler, and the enthusiasm for repurchase of shares is greater.
Repurchasing shares in a relatively low position is also conducive to improving the efficiency of the use of funds by listed companies, thereby increasing the profitability of each share, increasing the yield on net assets, and reducing the pressure on the company's profit index.
Compared with the increase in the holdings of major shareholders, the significance of the repurchase of shares by listed companies is greater, and also reflects the willingness of listed companies to manage their active market capitalization and abundant cash flow.
Xu Yang believes that the undervaluation of stock prices is the main factor in the repurchase of listed companies, and the company's share price has been unable to reflect the company's future development prospects, so such companies deserve investors' attention, but they can't blindly invest, and they need to pay attention to the financial reports of such listed companies and the specific business situation.
Listed companies with large-scale repurchase behavior at least indicate the company's development confidence and financial strength.
A-share listed company repurchase enthusiasm gradually warmed up, but also normalized the repurchase behavior, data show that nearly a thousand listed companies have implemented share repurchases this year, and leading companies in various industries have become the main force of the repurchase market.
China Ping An's recent disclosure of repurchase progress said that the company has accumulated the repurchase of A shares of 57.59 million shares through centralized bidding transactions, accounting for 0.35% of the total amount of funds paid, the total amount of funds paid has been totaling 50 billion yuan (excluding transaction fees), and the repurchase of shares will be all used for employee stock ownership plans, including but not limited to the long-term service plan that the company's shareholders' meeting has been considered and adopted.
