The deepest record of China's railway tunnel shaft was set
China News Agency and Insurance Mountain September 27th (Zhang Weiming Xu for Guozhou Jingbo) After more than 1200 days of day and night construction, the construction of the Da (Li) Railway Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel 1 shaft was completed on the 27th, the depth of the underground 762.59 meters below the ground, breaking the deepest record of the Chinese railway tunnel shaft, and this record was created in a large number of gushing water.
The full length of 34.5 kilometers of the Great Rui Railway Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel is located in Yunnan, the tunnel from the west bank of the river crossing the Gaoligong Mountain Mountains, is the longest tunnel in the two lines of the Asian double-lined single-hole tunnel.
The tunnel traverses the 19 fracture zone and is buried up to 1155 meters deep, because it covers almost all tunnel construction may encounter adverse geology and major risks, and the Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel is known as the "geological museum" of tunnel construction.
The shaft is the most important auxiliary pit road in the Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel, and is responsible for increasing the operational surface to achieve "long tunnel short" and the important task of ventilating the operation of the railway.
1 shaft successfully dug to the bottom of the well, marking the high-rigo cave into the tunnel officially into the horizontal tunnel construction, to be dug at the bottom of the well and the replacement of equipment, the underground can be added to four work surfaces, speed up the tunnel positive hole excavation speed.
"The shaft is all in the granite formation, because the granite formation is more cracked, can't stop the water, from the top to the downs and downs, basically how much deep the well is how much is the pressure."
Jingzhao, chief engineer of the Dalian Railway Project Department of the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, told reporters that in the construction of the shaft, there have been many times in the mud surge, collapse and other dangerous situations, and the construction party invites experts to take the pulse on the spot, and more than 20 seminars and treatment plans.
"When the water in the shaft is the largest, it is more than 300 cubic meters per hour, and the bottom of the deep well is more than 700 meters, and the water pressure is equivalent to the bottom of the sea floor of 700 meters deep."
"If you do not drain in time, it will flood the wells in one hour, and we spend almost 85% of the time to cure water, and 15% time is used to dig in."
In order to overcome the longitudinal development of the shaft rock, the longitudinal development of the shaft, the surge of mud, and the granite, the tunnel construction adopts the system water treatment measures combined with "detection, injection and excavation" to reduce the construction risk.
After many improvements, the construction of the 1st shaft has formed a mechanized assembly line such as excavation system, out of the system, suspension system, and winch upgrading system, and realized the whole process of mechanization such as eye-catching, blasting, laying out, template installation, concrete pouring, etc., and accelerating the construction progress.
Eventually, after more than 1200 days and nights of construction, the shaft successfully completed the excavation of the depth of 762.59 meters.
The Great Rui Railway is an important part of the China-Myanmar International Passage and an important transportation infrastructure for the implementation of the Belt and Road Initiative.
After the completion of the car, Dali to Ruili's driving time will be shortened from six hours to the current highway, which will greatly improve the transportation pattern in the western region of Yunnan, and promote economic and trade cooperation and personnel-friendly exchanges between China and South and Southeast Asian countries.
