After the reform, the approval process is compressed from the six links of the previous "registration, acceptance, on-site verification, sampling inspection, material review, approval and certification" to the "registration, acceptance, approval and certification", and the completion time is shortened from 20 working days before the reform to the on-site completion.
Taking into account the high degree of export characteristics of Pudong's economy, the Shanghai market supervision department decentralizes the registration authority of the permanent representative office of foreign (regional) enterprises to the Shanghai Free Trade Zone, which is convenient for enterprises to handle it nearby.
