Chinese students can apply for German undergraduate students with college entrance examination results
Recently, the Anabin database, which is responsible for the evaluation of foreign academic qualifications in Germany, announced on the official website: Starting in 2020, Chinese high school graduates can apply directly for German undergraduate students with college entrance examination results, and do not need to register in domestic universities first.
Prior to this, Chinese high school graduates who want to apply to German universities need to study for one semester (211,985 University) or three semesters (ordinary undergraduates) in China, and pass the APS review or TestAS exam.
The release of the new regulations, or will save at least half a year for Chinese students who are willing to study in Germany.
It is reported that the new regulations will take effect in the second half of 2019.
Applicants need to meet: complete the 12th formal compulsory education, obtain the high school diploma; participate in the examination, college entrance examination, and the college entrance examination score to reach 70% of the total score and above (if the total score of 750 points, it is necessary to reach more than 525 points), and it contains two language achievements and a mathematics or natural science performance and other requirements.
In addition, the specific professional requirements for college entrance examination results are not the same.
For example, applying for medicine, oral medicine, veterinary medicine, pharmacy and other majors, the college entrance examination score must reach a full score of 80%, and the college entrance examination subjects must include mathematics, physics, chemistry, biology at least two, or participate in comprehensive management; apply for a legal profession, college entrance examination scores need to reach a full score of 80%, and the college entrance examination subjects must include at least two categories in foreign language, history, geography, or participate in the comprehensive.
According to incomplete statistics, there are currently a number of countries, including Germany, the United Kingdom, Canada, Australia and other countries to recognize the results of the Chinese college entrance examination.
In the United Kingdom, for example, universities such as Cambridge University, Birmingham University, and the University of Leicester have accepted Chinese students to apply for study with their college entrance examination results.
