State Council Information Office Releases White Paper on China and World in the New Era
On the occasion of the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, the Information Office of the State Council released the white paper "China and the World in the New Era" on the 27
Xu Lin, vice minister of China and director of the State Council's Information Office, said that the white paper around issues such as "where does China come from, where it goes", "what kind of world China promotes to build" and "how China develops how to get along with the world", systematically introduces China's development achievements, development path and development direction, and deeply expounds China's relations with the world, so as to enhance the international community's understanding and understanding of China's development.
