A villager in Baokang County, Hubei Province, hunts for wild animals, was ordered to "compulsory mountain patrol"
A villager in Baokang County, Hubei Province, was sentenced to death for hunting wild animals, and ordered him to compensate for the cost of ecological resource environmental damage restoration of 15420 yuan (yuan, the same below).
Due to the poverty of the defendant's family, the procuratorial organs have activated the cost of alternative labor compensation for ecological restoration, and achieved the organic unity of legal and social effects.
Wang Zhongliang, deputy attorney general of Baokang County Procuratorate, introduced on the 27th that through alternative labor such as "compulsory patrol" for three months, the defendant Zhou has established a deep feeling with the wild macaque monkeys and is deeply responsible for the previous hunting animal behavior.
On June 21st this year, a criminal incidental civil public interest lawsuit filed by the Baokang County Procuratorate filed a criminal incidental civil public interest lawsuit in the field of ecological resources, which was heard in public in the county court and sentenced in court.
The defendant Zhou was sentenced to three years in prison, suspended for four years, and punished him with a fine of 3000 yuan, and ordered him to compensate for the cost of ecological resource environmental damage restoration of 15420 yuan.
After investigation, Zhou began to set up a power grid on the cliffs in late January 2014, and has hunted more than 20 wild animals, including antelope, small suede, crown deer and so on.
The antelope belongs to the national secondary endangered wildlife protection animals, and the small suede and crowned deer are listed as the National Land Wildlife Protection List.
During the trial, Zhou confessed to his illegal facts and actions, and was willing to bear civil liability.
However, considering the poor economic situation of Zhou's family, under the coordination of the Baokang County Procuratorate, the local village committee, forest station, and Zhou reached an agreement on the cost of alternative labor compensation ecological restoration: that is, Zhou Mou carried out macaque domestication management work, compulsory mountain patrolling, and forest protection for one year, and provided public welfare services to meet the cost of ecological restoration.
For the prosecutor's recommendation, the court agreed that Zhou's execution of suspended sentences at the same time, actively fulfill the obligation of "alternative labor compensation for ecological restoration costs."
At present, Zhou has been in the macaque reserve compulsory labor for three months, the mountain patrol is active, good performance.
