In April this year, the Guiding Opinions on Promoting the Development of Care Services for Infant and Young Children Under the Age of 3rd issued by the General Office of the State Council had a relevant description of the joint parenting of husband and wife.
In the process of revising the Regulations, Ningxia introduced the innovation "to encourage employers to give each year to ten days of common parental leave for couples who have children in accordance with the laws and regulations, and during the child to the age of three weeks, they are given each day of mutual parental leave every year."
At the same time, the Regulations highlight anti-sexual harassment and the protection of women minors.
In article 43 of the Regulations, it incorporates the latest legislative achievements in the current compilation of the personality rights of China's civil code, and details the constituent elements of sexual harassment and the main body and mechanism of anti-sexual harassment.
Article 44 of the Ordinance is expressly prohibited for frequent sexual assault of girls, and requires educational institutions to carry out relevant education, protection and prevention work, which will become a new benchmark for the protection of girls in local legislation.
In view of women's right to know and dispose of the common property of marriage and family, article 35 of the Regulations clearly stipulates that women's right to know about common property and the obligations of property registration agencies and related subjects, and provides solid institutional support for women's rights protection.
In addition, in response to social hot issues - gender discrimination in employment - article 26 of the Regulations not only prohibits direct discrimination, but also orders the prohibition of indirect discrimination, and absorbs the latest practical experience of joint interviews, enhances the punishment of gender discrimination violations, and more vigorously safeguards women's legitimate rights and interests.
In recent years, the Ningxia Women's Federation, the Joint Public Prosecutor's Law Department, Civil Affairs and other departments have promoted and introduced social professional forces to participate in the mediation of marital and family conflicts and anti-domestic violence, which has achieved remarkable results.
The Regulations summarize and enhance this, and in a number of laws, encourage the mobilization of social forces and the accumulation of social resources to jointly safeguard the rights and interests of women, and require people's governments at or above the county level to provide stable and institutional guarantees and support through the purchase of services.
