Liu Kun, Minister of Finance: 67 central enterprises and financial institutions have transferred to the state-owned 8601 billion yuan to enrich the social security fund.
Finance Minister Liu Kun said on the 27th that so far, 67 central enterprises and central financial institutions have completed the transfer of some state-owned capital enrichment social security funds, and the total amount of state-owned capital transferred is about 8601 billion yuan.
Liu Kun made the above statement at the meeting on the same day by the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security, and the SASAC jointly held a number of national transfer of state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund work task deployment.
"The transfer of some state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund is an important measure to reform and improve the basic pension insurance system, and it is a full manifestation of the intergenerational fairness of the development results of state-owned enterprises and the intergenerational fairness of the basic pension insurance system, and is a policy measure based on the current and long-term consideration."
In 2017, the State Council issued the Implementation Plan for Transferring Some State-owned Capital Enriching Social Security Funds, which requires the selection of some central enterprises and some provinces to carry out pilot projects.
According to Liu Kun, the pre-transfer work has achieved positive results.
At the central level, three batches of a total of 67 central enterprises and central financial institutions have been transferred, and the total amount of state-owned capital transferred is about 8601 billion yuan.
Among them, the transfer of central financial institutions whose functions of the Ministry of Finance fulfills the duties of funders has been basically completed.
The transfer of central enterprises has a certain scale.
At the local level, the preliminary work of enterprises transfer has been carried out successively.
As of the end of 2018, the pilot work in Zhejiang and Yunnan provinces was basically completed, transferring state-owned capital of 158 billion yuan and 185 billion yuan respectively.
In addition to the pilot provinces, other provinces have also carried out pre-transfer preparatory work, laying the foundation for the next step of the implementation of the transfer.
According to the joint issuance of notices by the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security, the SASAC, the State Administration of Taxation and the Securities Regulatory Commission, the work of the central and local governments to transfer some of the state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund was fully launched in 2019 and basically completed by the end of 2020.
The meeting held on the same day made a specific deployment of the comprehensive transfer work.
The meeting stressed the need to complete the transfer work pragmatically and efficiently.
"According to the schedule, the transfer work should be basically completed by the end of 2020."
Transfer working hours are tight and the task is heavy. ”
Liu Kun said that all regions and departments should carefully organize and carefully arrange to ensure that the transfer work should be completed as required; solidly promote the work, accurately grasp the transfer policy content; strengthen communication and coordination, and solve difficult problems in a timely manner.
State-owned capital transfer to enrich the social security fund - starting from the starting point of "enriching the social security fund money bag", the destination is to provide strong support for the pension security.
However, the author believes that this is not a simple "physical displacement" of equity, but the "mathematical addition" is opened.
On September 20th, the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Human and Social Affairs, the SASAC, the General Administration of Taxation and the Securities Regulatory Commission jointly issued the "Notice on Comprehensively Promoting the Transfer of Part of the State-owned Capital to Enrich the Work of the Social Security Fund", which clarified the timetable for the transfer of state-owned social security funds, that is, the central and local transfer of some state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund.
After the release of the document, the Ministry of Finance and other departments implemented it soon.
On September 25, the Ministry of Finance transferred all 10% of the equity stakes held by the Industrial and Commercial Bank and the Agricultural Bank to the Social Security Fund, and the total value of the two shares was more than 11.5 billion yuan.
According to the regulations, the Social Security Foundation, as a financial investor, enjoys the right of income, disposal and right to know the state-owned equity.
In its announcement, ICBC and Agricultural Bank said that this change in equity will not cause changes to the shareholders and actual controllers of the Bank.
In this regard, the author believes that similar equity transfer of state-owned enterprises is not a simple change in equity ownership, but can stimulate a series of "additional operations" that can stimulate a series of effects.
The first step of some state-owned enterprises to transfer social security "additional results", which is naturally a way to reflect the ownership of state-owned enterprises and the development results are shared by the whole people.
After years of reform and development, state-owned enterprises, especially central enterprises, are in important industries and fields in China's economy, and the overall profitability is stronger and relatively stable.
Among them, leading enterprises are continuing to achieve better and bigger and stronger.
On July 10th, the executive meeting of the State Council decided to comprehensively launch the transfer of some state-owned capital to enrich the work of the Social Security Fund this year.
The Ministry of Finance immediately said that it will work with relevant departments and in accordance with the deployment of the executive meeting of the State Council to do a good job in comprehensively promoting the transfer of some state-owned capital to enrich the social security fund, fully reflecting the intergenerational fairness of the basic pension insurance system and the development of state-owned enterprises.
The second step of the transfer of "additional results" is to enhance the sustainability of China's social security fund and further consolidate the foundation of the pension social security system.
With the aging of the population, China's social security funds are facing pressure, and most of the state-owned capital, as the subject of the transfer, most of them have the ability to maintain profitability and dividend, not only can effectively supplement the social security fund, but also provide the source of living water for the social security fund.
Some calculations show that for every 13.8 percentage point state-owned capital transferred, the proportion of deposits in basic pension insurance can be supported by one percentage point of reduction.
The third step of the transfer, "additional results", is to increase the stabilizer for the capital market.
The way to transfer the main body to obtain income is "redifice-oriented, supplemented by operation".
As a financial investor in state-owned capital, the Social Security Fund does obtain equity dividend income.
However, as a value investor in the capital market, the Social Security Fund has a strong ability to operate capital.
For listed assets in state-owned capital, the participation of social security funds in holding shares will further optimize the governance structure of listed companies, which will help improve the operating level of enterprises and have a positive impact on listed companies and capital markets.
At the same time, the Social Security Fund, as a bellwether for investment vane, is conducive to further enhancing its influence in the market and playing a role as a "stabilizer" in the market.
In addition, it is also conducive to giving full play to the "value discovery" function of institutional investors and guiding investors to rational investment and value investment.
