Overseas peace is no small matter, a leaf of total concern.
Cui Aimin said that in the past seven decades, the number of Chinese citizens "going out" has increased sharply, from the "annual average of less than one million" before the reform and opening up to the current hundred million people every year. At the same time, the safety of Chinese citizens' overseas travel is more secure, and the work objects of consular protection and assistance have also expanded from overseas Chinese to overseas Chinese to overseas Chinese, tourists, international students, and migrant workers.
