In a dangerous moment, the motherland can take you home; if you want to "walk on a trip", it is no longer a dream.
According to Cui Aimin, as of the end of August this year, China has concluded a mutual visa exemption agreement with 14 countries covering ordinary passport holders.
In addition, more and more countries have unilaterally granted Chinese citizens visa-free or visa-on-arrival access to the country.
Forty-two countries and regions, such as Thailand and Egypt, unilaterally grant visas to Chinese citizens with ordinary passports, while 15 other countries and regions, such as Indonesia, unilaterally allow Chinese citizens with ordinary passports to enter the country without visa.
