As of the end of August, China has reached agreements or arrangements to simplify visa procedures with 41 countries.
These include the two-year multi-time visa issued by the United States, Canada, Israel and Argentina for each other for tourism and business personnel, and the issuance of two-year multiple visa arrangements for each other's travel, business and family visitation with the United Kingdom.
The United Kingdom and Belgium jointly launched a "visa one-stop" service, with France, Italy and Singapore reducing visa acceptance times to 48 hours, 36 hours and 24 hours, respectively.
For business people who often go abroad, the APEC business travel card that has entered the country multiple times and has convenient customs clearance is a good choice.
According to Cui Aimin, holding the travel card is equivalent to obtaining a multi-year visa for 16 economies around the Asia-Pacific region for five years, which is of great significance to business personnel, especially private enterprise personnel, "going out".
At present, China's effective card holdings rank first among APEC economies.
The Ministry of Foreign Affairs will actively negotiate bilateral visa reciprocity agreements, promote more countries to adopt visa facilitation measures for Chinese citizens, so that the results of diplomatic work will be more translated into measures to benefit the people and facilitate the people, and continuously improve the "gold content" of Chinese passports.
