The reporter learned from the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences on the 27th that at present, the night moth of Yunnan grassland has been effectively prevented and controlled, and it has not caused a large-scale outbreak to a disaster, and the prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In January this year, Jiangcheng County, Pu'er City, Yunnan Province, for the first time found a grassy night moths that had been moved from outside the country, and then confirmed that the occurrence of grassland night moths in 129 counties in Yunnan, which also spread from Yunnan to mainland China, posing a direct threat to China's food production.
Grassy night moth is an important agricultural pest of multi-food long-range migration originating in tropical and subtropical regions of the Americas. It is a major migratory pest for the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations. It is a major migratory pest for the global early warning of the United Nations.
The pest endangers more than 80 crops such as corn, sugar cane and sorghum, and the amount of food is large, which can cause losses of up to 70% of production.
Prevention and control is difficult, China does not have the registered pesticide to prevent the insect.
Since the migration of grassy night moths into Yunnan, the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences has sent a researcher to Chen Aidong, leading the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Cross-border Pests Collaborative Green Prevention and Control Provincial Innovation Team to go to the front line, field investigation, collect samples, and carry out technical guidance and test demonstration.
Chen Aidong's team has initially grasped the population characteristics of Yunnan grassy night moths, natural enemy insect resources, overseas pest source characteristics, population relocation trajectory, drug virulence and field prevention and control effect.
They actively carry out the research and application of green prevention and control technology, through the implementation of new green prevention and control technologies such as population monitoring, insect booby trapping, scientific medicine and agronomic measures, the prevention and control effect in the demonstration area has reached more than 90%, while reducing the use of chemical pesticides, protecting natural enemy resources and ecological environment, and providing technical guarantee for Yunnan to effectively control the outbreak of night moths and sustainable governance of grasslands.
At present, Yunnan grassland greedy night moth has been effectively controlled, did not cause a large-scale outbreak into a disaster, and the prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In the next step, the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences will focus on the ecological mechanism of population relocation and invasion, and break through the construction of biological control and green prevention and control technology system.
At the same time, we will actively promote cross-border international cooperation, and strive to establish joint key laboratories and joint monitoring outlets and demonstration zones overseas to enhance the comprehensive monitoring and early warning capabilities of Yunnan grassland night moths.
