The 86th China-Laos-Myanmar-Thailand Mekong River Joint Patrol Law Enforcement was completed.
The reporter learned from the press office of the Yunnan Provincial Public Security Bureau on the 27th that at 15: 30 a.m. on the same day, the three law enforcement boats in China and the two law enforcement boats involved in the 86th China-Myanmar-Thai Mekong River Joint Patrol and the two law enforcement boats in China were successfully berthed, marking the successful conclusion of the joint patrol law enforcement operation.
The operation was launched in Guanzhou on the 24th, and lasted for four days and nights, and a total of 136 law enforcement personnel were sent by the four countries of China and Myanmar, and six law enforcement boats were sent.
During the operation, the formations carried out joint patrols, anti-drug propaganda and other activities in key waters such as the Golden Triangle, Laoban and Mengmo.
In addition, the Chinese side has also sent a police actual combat instructor to the Lao People's Army 122 and 133 border defense companies to carry out police practical combat skills exchanges, effectively improving the emergency response capacity of law enforcement personnel of the two sides to jointly deal with emergencies.
China, Myanmar and Thailand also held law enforcement cooperation and exchange meetings in Qingsheng, Thailand, to inform each other about the recent situation of countries in border management, drug crime and the security situation in the Mekong River basin, and to hold consensus on strengthening information exchange, research and law enforcement cooperation, and to hold four national cultural exchanges to carry out competition projects such as football, rattan, iron ball and tug-of-war, and effectively enhance mutual understanding among law enforcement players and the cooperation friendship between law enforcement members.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Water Patrol Corps of the Yunnan Provincial Public Security Department, after the operation, the two sides will continue to carry out a ten-day joint training and segmented joint patrol tasks to improve the Mekong River alert rate and make every effort to maintain the security and stability of the Mekong River Basin.
Commander of the Thai side said that since the launch of the Mekong Joint Patrol Law Enforcement, the four countries have close exchanges, deepened practical cooperation, and achieved fruitful results in law enforcement and security cooperation and cultural exchanges.
It is hoped that the quadrilateral law enforcement cooperation will continue to deepen and expand, and strive to open a new situation of law enforcement cooperation between the four countries and make new contributions to maintaining the security and stability of the Mekong River Basin.
